  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Femoroacetabular Impingement (FAI) describes a condition of the hip where additional bone
      results in the abutment of the femoral neck against the rim of the acetabulum. This gives
      rise to localised cartilage damage and pain, but also increases the risk of developing
      osteoarthritis. The purpose of this study is to compare the effectiveness of arthroscopic
      surgery versus physiotherapy and activity modification for the treatment of this condition.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
